{
  "abstract": "A review of the pests and pest caused losses in pigeonpea (Cajanus cajan L. Millsp.) grown in\r\ndifferent parts of the World is given. At Patancheru (Andhra Pradesh, India1 pest damage assessments\r\non some pigeonpea cultivars during 1975-77 showed that about 80% of the pigeonpea flowers\r\nwere shed without setting pods and up to 32% of the shea flowers were found to he attacked by\r\nInsects. The relationship of the plants growth habit and the maturity period of the crop to the\r\nattack and damage by various pests is explained. A summary of pest damage recorded during extensive\r\nsurveys of farmers' fields in India during 1975-81 is furnished.",
